{
	"Name": "Auditd Suspicious C2 Command Patterns",
	"Description": "Detects suspicious command-and-control patterns in command execution. Works with standard auditd logs (PROCTITLE records) without requiring custom configuration. Detects: wget/curl piped to shell, downloads to suspicious locations (/tmp, /dev/shm), base64 decode to execution, nc/netcat reverse shells, SSH tunneling, suspicious nmap scans. Covers MITRE ATT\u0026CK techniques: Application Layer Protocol (T1071), Non-Application Layer Protocol (T1095), Data Encoding (T1132), Remote Services (T1021), Network Service Scanning (T1046).",
